20are%20fed%20up%20with%20swiping%20and%20looking%20for%20more%20meaningful%20ways%20to%20connect.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20time%20to%20consider%20a%20time-honored%20tradition%3A%20Matchmaking.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Caside%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDo%20you%20have%20a%20story%20to%20share%3F%20Contact%20this%20reporter%20at%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Ajkaplan%40businessinsider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ejkaplan%40businessinsider.com%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Faside%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22aac900de-06ec-4e07-846a-4e1bcec2a211%5C%22%3ESetting%20up%20your%20friends%20is%20a%20public%20service%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ETerence%20Philpotts%20is%20a%20single%2041-year-old%20promoter%20who%20lives%20in%20North%20Carolina.%20He's%20an%20avid%20traveler%20and%20would%20love%20to%20meet%20someone%20new%20in%20person.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPeople%20simply%20don't%20go%20out%20as%20much%20as%20they%20used%20to%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20I%20mean%2C%20I'm%20just%20as%20at%20fault%20as%20anyone%20else.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPhilpotts%20said%20that%20his%20best%20relationship%20came%20from%20being%20set%20up%20by%20a%20mutual%20friend%2C%20and%20he's%20open%20to%20trying%20it%20again.%20After%20all%2C%20dating%20is%20expensive%2C%20he%20said.%20And%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdating-nightmare-tea-whisper-network-apps-save-us-2025-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Erisky%3C%2Fa%3E%3B%20a%20setup%20is%20more%20efficient.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20person%20knows%20both%20of%20us%2C%20they%20know%20our%20nuances%2C%20they%20know%20what%20we%2C%20what%20we%20don't%20like%2C%20and%20most%20people%20would%20think%20that%20they%20would%20find%20their%20friends%20compatible%20with%20each%20other%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20that's%20basically%20what%20happened%20there.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EExperiences%20like%20Philpotts'%20used%20to%20be%20a%20lot%20more%20common%2C%20but%20the%20apps%20took%20over%20as%20the%20dominant%20matchmaker%20for%20heterosexual%20couples%20in%20the%202000s%2C%20per%20the%20findings%20of%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pnas.org%2Fdoi%2Ffull%2F10.1073%2Fpnas.1908630116%23data-availability%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eseminal%20study%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20Proceedings%20of%20the%20National%20Academy%20of%20Sciences.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20brought%20with%20them%20a%20new%20dilemma%3A%20the%20pen%20pal%20stage.%20Scott%20Sibley%2C%20a%20professor%20at%20Northern%20Illinois%20University%20who%20teaches%20human%20development%20and%20family%20sciences%20%E2%80%94%20as%20well%20as%20being%20a%20licensed%20marriage%20and%20family%20therapist%20%E2%80%94%20said%20that%20one%20of%20the%20big%20hurdles%20facing%20daters%20is%20a%20prolonged%20talking%20stage.%20Potential%20daters%20are%20substituting%20dates%20for%20digital%20conversation%20instead.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThough%20Sibley's%20research%20on%20relationships%20found%20that%20singles%20want%20to%20move%20beyond%20the%20talking%20stage%2C%20they're%20hamstrung%20by%20a%20fear%20of%20rejection.%20It's%20easier%20to%20hide%20behind%20a%20never-ending%20conversation%20than%20it%20is%20to%20actually%20get%20out%20there.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat's%20the%20funny%20thing%2C%26quot%3B%20Sibley%20said.%20%26quot%3BThey'd%20rather%20be%20going%20on%20dates%20and%20being%20asked%20on%20dates.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20mismatch%20between%20expectations%20and%20reality%20could%20be%20fueling%20the%20loneliness%20epidemic.%20According%20to%20a%20Gallup%20survey%20of%206%2C289%20Americans%20from%20August%20through%20September%202024%2C%20around%20a%20fifth%20of%20US%20adults%20said%20that%20they%20had%20experienced%20loneliness%20a%20lot%20in%20the%20previous%20day.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FboOGz%2Fembed.js%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22feedlyNoScript%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FboOGz%2Ffull.png%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20seem%20to%20be%20taking%20some%20proactive%20action%3B%20the%20latest%20data%20from%20the%20Bureau%20of%20Labor%20Statistics'%20American%20Time%20Use%20Survey%20shows%20that%20younger%20Americans%20are%20spending%20less%20time%20alone%2C%20although%20they're%20still%20spending%20far%20more%20time%20solo%20than%20they%20did%20prior%20to%20the%20pandemic.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FXU99t%2Fembed.js%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22feedlyNoScript%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FXU99t%2Ffull.png%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20you%20can%20help%20do%20your%20part%20to%20fight%20America's%20dating%20drought%2C%20Damona%20Hoffman%2C%20a%20Los%20Angeles-based%20dating%20coach%2C%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPeople%20are%20so%20down%20on%20dating%20apps%20right%20now%20and%20are%20looking%20for%20ways%20to%20connect%20offline%20or%20feeling%20nostalgic%20for%20an%20old-fashioned%20meet-cute%20cute%20so%20why%20not%20try%20your%20hand%20at%20making%20a%20match%3F%26quot%3B%20Hoffman%20said.%20%26quot%3BEven%20if%20they%20don't%20end%20up%20madly%20in%20love%2C%20they%20could%20make%20a%20meaningful%20connection%20in%20another%20way%20or%20become%20friends.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDaniel%20Cox%2C%20the%20director%20of%20the%20Survey%20Center%20on%20American%20Life%20at%20the%20American%20Enterprise%20Institute%2C%20is%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.americansurveycenter.org%2Fnewsletter%2Fbook-announcement-uncoupled%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewriting%20a%20book%3C%2Fa%3E%20about%20the%20growing%20divide%20between%20men%20and%20women%2C%20especially%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20dating.%20He%20said%20that%20what%20they've%20been%20hearing%20is%20that%20the%20online%20experience%20is%20%26quot%3Bterrible.%26quot%3B%20Folks%20are%20more%20likely%20to%20treat%20each%20other%20as%20expendable%20in%20what%20seems%20like%20an%20infinite%20sea%20of%20choices.%20That's%20where%20a%20return%20to%20form%2C%20or%20an%20embrace%20of%20a%20new%20form%20of%20dating%2C%20might%20come%20in.%20Cox's%20research%20has%20found%20that%20young%20women%20are%20especially%20more%20likely%20to%20date%20through%20their%20social%20circles.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere's%20a%20recognition%20that%20we%20have%20a%20better%20chance%20of%20success%20or%20at%20least%20a%20better%20chance%20of%20success%2C%20or%20at%20least%20a%20better%20chance%20of%20having%20a%20good%20time%20if%20we're%20dating%20people%20who%20are%20friends%20of%20friends%2C%26quot%3B%20Cox%20said%2C%20%26quot%3Bpeople%20who%20are%20in%20our%20social%20circle%2C%20who%20have%20some%20sense%20of%20obligation%20to%20treat%20us%20well%20and%20respectfully.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22b83c74d8-b307-404d-9d3b-f4d9cbf3525e%5C%22%3EHow%20to%20set%20up%20your%20friends%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EHow%20people%20meet%20has%20evolved%2C%20but%20the%20trajectory%20of%20relationships%20still%20follows%20a%20standard%20formula.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBrian%20Ogolsky%2C%20a%20professor%20of%20human%20development%20and%20family%20studies%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Illinois%20Urbana-Champaign%2C%20summarized%20it%20like%20this%3A%20we%20meet%2C%20we%20flirt%2C%20we%20do%20the%20dance%20around%20defining%20the%20relationship%2C%20we%20end%20it%2C%20or%20become%20exclusive.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAs%20long%20as%20I've%20been%20studying%20relationships%2C%20which%20is%20now%20pushing%2030%20years%2C%20and%20even%20when%20we%20look%20at%20historical%20ways%2C%20that%20trajectory%20looks%20sort%20of%20very%20similar%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHoffman%20said%20that%20a%20good%20setup%20should%20rest%20on%20what%20she%20deems%20the%20four%20pillars%20of%20long-term%20compatibility%3A%20%26quot%3BCommon%20goals%2C%20shared%20values%2C%20communication%20styles%2C%20and%20mutual%20respect.%26quot%3B%20Look%20past%20what%20might%20be%20surface-level%20chemistry%20%E2%80%94%20like%20a%20shared%20love%20of%20sushi%20or%20hiking%20%E2%80%94%20and%20dig%20deeper%20into%20their%20beliefs%2C%20hopes%2C%20and%20openness%20to%20a%20relationship.%20As%20a%20friend%2C%20you%20may%20have%20unique%20insight%20into%20that.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAmy%20Nobile%20Messing%2C%20a%20dating%20coach%20based%20in%20New%20York%2C%20said%20that%20if%20you're%20setting%20up%20a%20friend%2C%20you%20should%20ask%20for%20their%20elevator%20pitch%20%E2%80%94%20a%20paragraph%20about%20themselves%20and%20maybe%20a%20photo%20to%20share.%20The%20other%20person%20should%20do%20the%20same%3B%20there%20should%20be%20no%20surprises.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20so%2C%20as%20Hoffman%20said%2C%20singles%20should%20also%20solicit%20setups%20from%20folks%20in%20their%20orbit%3B%20Hoffman%20calls%20it%20their%20%26quot%3Bconnector's%20circle.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHoffman%20and%20Messing%20both%20agree%20that%20once%20you%20set%20up%20the%20friends%2C%20your%20job%20is%20done.%20If%20it%20doesn't%20work%20out%2C%20that's%20fine.%20You%20shouldn't%20end%20up%20in%20a%20position%20where%20you're%20fielding%20feedback%20or%20trying%20to%20control%20the%20situation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOf%20course%2C%20setting%20up%20your%20friends%20is%20not%20necessarily%20a%20bulletproof%20solution.%20As%20Anna%20Goldfarb%2C%20the%20author%20of%20%26quot%3BModern%20Friendship%3A%20How%20to%20Nurture%20Our%20Most%20Valued%20Connections%2C%26quot%3B%20said%2C%20there's%20always%20the%20risk%20that%20your%20friend%20sets%20you%20up%20with%20someone%20who%20ends%20up%20being%20a%20dud%2C%20or%20your%20friends%20who%20get%20together%20break%20up%20and%20create%20a%20sticky%20social%20situation.%20There's%20also%20the%20unpredictable%20nature%20of%20when%20sparks%20fly.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat's%20sort%20of%20the%20beauty%20of%20romance%20%E2%80%94%20sometimes%20there's%20these%20intangibles%20that%20I%20couldn't%20possibly%20predict%2C%26quot%3B%20Goldfarb%20said.%20%26quot%3BWith%20that%20said%2C%20my%20parents%20were%20set%20up%20on%20a%20blind%20date%20by%20friends%2C%20so%20I%20am%20here%20in%20this%20universe%20because%20of%20blind%20dates.%20I%20think%20it%20can%20happen.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20Vargas%2C%20who's%20been%20setting%20up%20her%20friend%20via%20Hinge%20from%20across%20the%20country%2C%20the%20exercise%20has%20led%20to%20some%20dates.%20While%20none%20have%20translated%20into%20a%20romantic%20relationship%20yet%2C%20it's%20led%20to%20new%20friendships%20and%20the%20ability%20to%20get%20to%20know%20the%20city%20better.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20feel%20like%20she's%20also%20gained%20a%20little%20bit%20more%20confidence%20in%20going%20on%20the%20dates%20and%20also%20just%20her%20ability%20to%20talk%20with%20people%20and%20see%2C%20oh%2C%20actually%20now%20I%20know%20I%20would%20rather%20prefer%20this%2C%20or%20I%20would%20want%20this%20instead%2C%26quot%3B%20Vargas%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdating-app-fatigue-setting-up-friends-2025-7%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1753602241000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6881452b3d5881a51c1de147%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdating-app-fatigue-setting-up-friends-2025-7%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Dating%20apps%20are%20leaving%20Americans%20lonelier%20than%20ever.%20We've%20lost%20the%20art%20of%20matchmaking%20%E2%80%94%20it's%20time%20to%20start%20setting%20up%20our%20friends.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22jkaplan%40businessinsider.com%20(Juliana%20Kaplan)%22%2C