%2Fjamtara-wilderness-camp-4-1753447168-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F07%2Fjamtara-wilderness-camp-4-1753447168-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F07%2Fjamtara-wilderness-camp-4-1753447168-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-476253%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EKailash%20Sankhala%20was%20chosen%20by%20Indira%20Gandhi%20to%20head%20Project%20Tiger%20initiative%20in%201973%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20around%201969%20when%20Kailash%20blew%20the%20whistle%20on%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F393021%2Fbilly-arjan-singh-wildlife-conservationist-dudhwa-forest-tiger-haven-society%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eplummeting%20tiger%20numbers%3C%2Fa%3E.%20He%20wasn%E2%80%99t%20the%20only%20one%20who%E2%80%99d%20noticed%20the%20red%20flag.%20A%20survey%20by%20Bombay%20Natural%20History%20Society%20had%20also%20noted%20the%20dip%2C%20compelling%20the%20IUCN%20(International%20Union%20for%20Conservation%20of%20Nature)%20to%20declare%20the%20tiger%20%E2%80%98endangered%E2%80%99.%20In%201972%2C%20things%20weren%E2%80%99t%20looking%20too%20good%3B%20the%20tiger%20census%20was%20just%20about%201%2C827.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAgainst%20this%20grim%20backdrop%2C%20Kailash%20was%20chosen%20by%20then-President%20Indira%20Gandhi%20to%20head%20the%20Project%20Tiger%20initiative%20in%201973.%20He%20was%20joined%20by%20then-cabinet%20minister%20Karan%20Singh.%20There%20was%20a%20monumental%20change%20that%20found%20its%20spark%20under%20their%20leadership%20%E2%80%94%20hunting%20was%20banned%2C%20reserves%20were%20created%2C%20and%20tiger%20numbers%20were%20resuscitated.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%201992%2C%20Kailash%20was%20awarded%20the%20Padma%20Shri%20for%20his%20contributions%20to%20tig