n.%20Elaborating%20on%20the%20design%2C%20Dhiraj%20shares%2C%20%E2%80%9CFifty%20percent%20of%20the%20terracotta%20used%20is%20recycled%2C%20making%20this%20one%20of%20the%20few%20buildings%20in%20Bengaluru%20to%20adopt%20such%20a%20high%20proportion%20of%20post-industrial%20terracotta.%20This%20porous%20terracotta%20screen%20contributes%20to%20a%20cooler%20microclimate%2C%20which%20is%20particularly%20important%20in%20the%20city%E2%80%99s%20increasingly%20warm%20urban%20fabric.%E2%80%9D%20He%20adds%20that%20recycled%20terracotta%20has%20significantly%20lower%20embodied%20energy%20than%20freshly%20manufactured%20materials.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EArchitects%2C%20take%20notes%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20While%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F334236%2Fclay-innovations-mitti-cool-fridge-terracotta-home-decor-mangalore-tiles-zero-electricity-cooler%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eterracotta%20is%20a%20versatile%20material%20to%20work%20with%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20there%20are%20certain%20things%20to%20keep%20in%20mind.%20Terracotta%E2%80%99s%20porosity%20means%20architects%20need%20to%20watch%20out%20for%20the%20weather%20patterns%20of%20the%20region%20since%20a%20terracotta%20facade%20would%20absorb%20water.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E3.%20Silica%20Composite%20Hollow%20Blocks%20(SCHB)%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%2014%2C000%20ft%20near%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%E2%80%99s%20Razdan%20Pass%2C%20where%20the%20winds%20and%20weather%20are%20harsh%2C%20there%E2%80%99s%20a%20symbol%20of%20resistance%20%E2%80%94%20and%20sustainability.%20It%E2%80%99s%20a%20bunker%20inspired%20by%20traditional%20sandbag%20construction.%20Designed%20by%20Gurugram-based%20R%2BD%20Studio%2C%20the%20hero%20material%20is%20Silica%20Composite%20Hollow%20Blocks%20(SCHB)%2C%20which%20are%20made%20up%20of%2080%20percent%20foundry%20dust%20and%2020%20percent%20plastic%20waste.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class